Task 0:  Simple web stack
Explanation:
https://imgur.com/a/P1b6MyA
- A server is the heart of the web infrastructure. Hosts the website. 
- DNS is the human-readable address of the website (www.foobar.com) and it transaltes to the IP address.
- DNS record type: CNAME (Canonical Name)
- The web server NGNIX: Handles HTTP requests and routes these to the application server.
- The application server: is like the brain behind the website. It handles all the logic and processing that happens behind the scenes.
- The Database: where data is managed and stored
- The servers communicates with the computer using network protocols(HTTP)
Issues:
1. SPOF
2. Downtime during maintenance
3. Cannot handle high traffic